===Etymology===
[[File:Beeswax.jpg|thumb|'''Beeswax''']]
From {{affix|en|bee|-s-|wax}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈbiːzwæks/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-beeswax.ogg|a=US}}
* {{rhymes|en|iːzwæks|s=2}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|+}}

# A [[wax]] [[secrete]]d by bees from which they make [[honeycomb]]; or, the processed form of this wax used in the manufacture of various goods.
#: {{ux|en|The candle was made entirely of natural '''beeswax'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|She polished the furniture with '''beeswax''' to give it a shine.}}
#: {{ux|en|The beekeeper collected honey and '''beeswax''' from the hives.}}
# {{lb|en|informal|North American|humorous}} ''[[business|Business]]'', as in such phrases as {{m|en|mind your own beeswax}} and {{m|en|none of your beeswax}}.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|mul|E901}} {{qualifier|when used as a [[glazing agent]]}}

